+*        UPSTREAM BUG FIX (vs ScaLAPACK 2.2.3): the original code passed
+*        M+ICOFFV as PBDTRAN's N argument while sizing WORK( IPV ) / LV
+*        from MPC20 = local rows of L. Whenever M > L (the typical case
+*        — M = K+L from PDORMRZ's caller), PBDTRAN's LDC contract
+*        `LDC >= NUMROC( N_arg, NBV, MYROW, ICROW2, NPROW )` fails
+*        because LV was sized for L rows, not M+ICOFFV rows. The
+*        transpose then exits via PXERBLA with INFO=11 ("LDC illegal
+*        value") *without* writing WORK( IPV ), and the outer DGEMM at
+*        the bottom of this branch multiplies uninitialised data into C
+*        — surfacing as a numerically corrupt result (typically a
+*        ~1.3x scaling error). Only the trailing K x L portion of V is
+*        meaningful per RZ's row-stored Householder convention, so the
+*        correct fix is to transpose the K x (L+ICOFFV) block instead
+*        of the K x (M+ICOFFV) block. The MPC20-sized IPV buffer then
+*        matches PBDTRAN's NP requirement under the alignment hypothesis
+*        IROFFC2 = ICOFFV (NB_V = MB_C). Documented in
+*        doc/UPSTREAM_BUGS.md.
+*
+         MQV0 = NUMROC( L+ICOFFV, NBV, MYCOL, IVCOL, NPCOL )
          IF( MYROW.EQ.ICROW2 ) THEN
             MPC20 = MPC2 + IROFFC2
          ELSE
             MPC20 = MPC2
          END IF
 *
-*        Locally V( IOFFV ) is K x MQV, C( IOFFC2 ) is MPC2 x NQC2
+*        Locally V( IOFFV ) is K x NQV, C( IOFFC2 ) is MPC2 x NQC2
 *        WORK( IPV ) is MPC20 x K = [ . V( IOFFV ) ]'
 *        WORK( IPW ) is K x MQV0  = [ . V( IOFFV ) ]
 *        WORK( IPT ) is the workspace for PBDTRAN
